Edition:
Quote:  We had not been in long, before one of the chiefs called on the girls to come and haka to the strangers, and in a few minutes a number of the prettiest young girls ... were seated in a circle in very shallow water ... They sang us a wild song ...  [ed fn] Short for haka taparahi, a term covering all dances and action songs ...
Notes:  1864 Dec Meade Ride through Disturbed Districts in 1959  Taylor Early Travellers 444


